author: Wl/odzisl/aw Duch and Karol Grudzi nski and Grzegorz Stawski
title: SYMBOLIC FEATURES IN NEURAL NETWORKS
venue: Department of Computer Methods, Nicolaus Copernicus University
window: Both FSM network and k-NN algorithm achieved similar results (within statistical accuracy) on the raw data as on the converted data (the number of attributes did not change here). On the Flags dataset, containing 194 samples, 3 continuous and 25 symbolic attributes, 8 classes (majority rate 30.8%) and no missing values, 10-fold cross-validation tests were performed. Large improvement is observed
